CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1954, pg. 13 reads: "Symposium Principals - When Atty. Carmel Carrington Marr, adviser to Ambassador Henry Cabot Lodge Jr., U.S. Representative to the United Nations, came here to be the main speaker at the National Achievement Clubs' annual Palm Sunday Symposium, she was tendered a luncheon by the family of steel executive Aaron Levinson, at his palatial home on Forbes Street...In the far right photo is shown the receiving line at the symposium at Loendi Club, at which Attorney Marr spoke..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, including one standing on right wearing dark dress with light colored cuffs and dark hat, holding eyeglasses, standing in receiving line in Loendi Club for Palm Sunday Symposium
